      "side": 1,
      "message": "I see that this commit https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/spdm/+/92060 has already been merged. If spdmd is started with a state directory, for example:\n\nspdmd --state-dir /path/to/your/dir\n\nand a policy.json file is placed in /path/to/your/dir, PolicyManager::load() will read it during startup and populate all the SPDM policy properties from it.\n\nThe JSON format is:\n\n{\n  \"Version\": 1.1,\n  \"Enabled\": true,\n  \"SecureSessionEnabled\": false,\n  \"VerifyCertificate\": true,\n  \"AllowExtendedAlgorithms\": false,\n  \"AllowedVersions\": [\"ALL\"],\n  \"AllowedAlgorithmsAEAD\": [\"ALL\"],\n  \"AllowedAlgorithmsBaseHash\": [\"ALL\"],\n  \"AllowedAlgorithmsBaseAsym\": [\"ALL\"]\n}\n\nGiven this, it seems we no longer need this commit, as we already have a mechanism to configure these settings based on platform requirements.",
